title: Remove [NO_REPLY] from AGENTS.md; make fully channel-conditional
---
Currently [NO_REPLY] is documented in AGENTS.md (always loaded) but only meaningful in group channels. Remove the [NO_REPLY] reference from AGENTS.md. Instead, inject the [NO_REPLY] suppression documentation only when the active channel type supports it. Depends on T003 (channel-conditional group chat section).